    "summary": "A 5.0 magnitude earthquake struck southwestern Iran's Khuzestan province on July 19, 2026. Emergency teams have been dispatched to assess damage in nearby villages.",
    "content": "A 5.0 magnitude earthquake struck the Saland area of Khuzestan province in southwestern Iran on July 19, 2026, according to Iranian state media IRIB. The quake's epicenter was located at a depth of 12 kilometers, and vibrations were felt across several neighboring districts.\n\nThe Iranian Red Crescent Society confirmed that rescue and assessment teams were quickly deployed to the affected zones. At least two teams have reached villages near the epicenter to evaluate the situation and provide aid if needed.\n\nKhuzestan province, which borders Iraq and the Persian Gulf, is no stranger to seismic activity. The region sits near tectonic fault lines, and earthquakes of similar magnitude have occurred in the past, often causing damage to poorly constructed buildings in rural areas.\n\nFor the Somali diaspora, many of whom maintain close ties to Iran due to historical trade and religious connections, this event serves as a reminder of the region's vulnerability to natural disasters. Somali communities in Iran or those with family there may be concerned about the safety of relatives.\n\nNo reports of casualties or major structural damage have been confirmed yet, but authorities remain on alert as aftershocks remain possible. The situation is being monitored by local officials and international observers.\n\nRead the original report from Goobjoog here: https://goobjoog.com/2026/07/19/dhulgariir-xooggan-oo-ku-dhuftay-gobolka-khuzestan-ee-dalka-iiraan/",
